No testable properties found in flask.typing.

The module `flask.typing` contains only type aliases and type definitions used for static type checking in Flask applications. These are not executable functions or classes - they're purely compile-time type hints with no runtime behavior. Type aliases like `ResponseReturnValue`, `RouteCallable`, and `ErrorHandlerCallable` cannot be tested with property-based testing as they don't perform any operations or transformations that could have properties to verify.
